access: To all those who visit Paris for the first time. Compared to other major European capitals or U.S. and Asian cities, Paris has a human scale and reasonable distances. It is even recommended, if you want to share the daily life of Parisians and French people.
interaction: Originally from Paris, fluent in English and German. As I am an heavy traveler myself, I could give you some good tips and tricks to make your stay in Paris the most memorable possible. Anyway if needed, just ask. I will always be available to respond.
house_rules: I do not have high expectations about house rules. My main wish is just that you respect this place as if it were your own. For the rest, nothing special, I'm pretty flexible if the requests are reasonable.

Woolwich is a district of South East London with a long and rich history.  A high amount of young professionals are residents in the area, among older people who have lived here for decades. Most of us work in the City-Bank, Canary Wharf, London Bridge, etc.  The things I love about where I live are: the museum at our door steps, the numerous heritage listed buildings in the neighbourhood, all complemented by several open parks, over 1km of river walks, and a rich history.  My advice to every guest is to always get off at the Woolwich Arsenal station and walk through the Royal Arsenal Development. host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

name: Retro 1 bed in Bermondsey
summary: A newly decorated retro apartment in trendy Bermondsey. Short walk to Bermondsey station and Tower Bridge. Lots of cool shops and restaurants around and the great Borough Market is not very far either.
space: Hi! I am Chris and I am delighted to welcome you to my home city - London! London never sleeps and there are so many amazing places to see, eat and drink at and absorb. And my flat located in Bermondsey is a great base for your London explorations.  The flat is located a mere 5 minutes walk from Bermondsey tube station which is on the Jubilee line. I call it the tourists line because all the major stops such as Westminster (Big Ben), Green Park (Buckhingham Palace), Bond Street, Baker Street (Sherlock Holmes Madam Tussauds's), London Bridge and Waterloo (London Eye) are on the Jubilee line.  Now coming back to the flat - this is a cosy little 1 bedroom on the ground floor of a purpose built building. The ground floor level is very convenient as you won't have to drag your bags up stairs! The flat is newly decorated with a mix of modern and vintage furniture. I love buying vintage items in antique markets and on ebay and I would love to give some recommendations on where to get the best

neighborhood_overview: Bermondsey is one of those places which will really make a difference to your stay in London. You will truly feel like you do belong to the city.  As well as the great restaurants on the uber trendy Bermonsey Street, you will find loads of exciting art initiatives like the White Cube, the Design Museum and the Fashion and Textile Museum. We have a great picture house on Bermondsey Square, a space which changes with the seasons and which every now and then, will surprise you with live music, parties, art, a farmers market and its famous antiques market. Another great development has been the market on Maltby Street which started with a few stalls and the excentric-in-a-good way vintage furniture shop Lassco and is now a very hype food market with excellent restaurants like St John's and the Spanish jamoneria Tozino. Definately worth a visit. The river enbankment is one of the most interesting parts of the whole river promenade. Just by walking along the street where the flat is you will
notes: The flat is on the ground floor.
transit: Bermondsey is the closest tube station and is about 5 minutes walk. It is on the Jubilee line which will take you to Waterloo and Westminster in 5-10 minutes! For Parking, there is a JustPark nearby too, outside the congestion zone!

host_about:
Hi, I'm Chris. A Londoner born and bred :) As they say 'if you're tired of London, you're tired of life' as there's so much to do here no matter what your interests.

London has fantastic sights and history. Wonderful bars and restaurants. And a vibrancy that matches any city in the world!

I love to travel and work for a travel company myself. I've been to over 40 countries in the last 10 years and my favourite of all was Japan

In Tokyo I stayed in a great Airbnb from which I explored the city like a local. I thought it was such a great idea I wanted to share my place with visitors to London so they could get an authentic experience of my city too!

I hope you like it. Let me know if you gave any questions

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: The Canary Wharf area is traditionally known to be the beating heart of London’s financial sector, full of tall buildings housing international banks. In recent years though, a large number of restaurants and bars have popped up in the area (and would be an easy 15-20 minute walk from the flat), such as Obica, Iberica, and Royal China. I particularly like Chai Ki, a modern Indian restaurant. You can also get drinks or have afternoon tea at the lovely Radisson Blu hotel nearby the apartment complex, which is a great setting to meet friends. Or, you can just use the kitchen in the apartment to cook yourself a meal and enjoy a nice comfy stay. With an iconic skyline towering over London, striking and dynamic architecture and a vibrant, cosmopolitan feel, Canary Wharf is firmly established as a first class shopping and leisure destination There are plenty of bars, pubs, restaurants, luxury stores to shop and a massive shopping mall. neighborhood_overview: The apartment is as mentioned located right by Superkilen/The Black Square and it is a very lively place in the spring and summer - fortunately without too much noise in the evening. Stretching some 750 meters along either side of a public cycle track and covering a total area of some 30,000 square meters, the park has three color-coded segments each semi-autonomous environments with their own programmatic and atmospheric agendas. The red square, painted bright red, orange and pink, focuses on recreation and modern living. "The black market" at the center just outside my front door is the park’s square features a rolling landscape that is emblazoned with a mesh of white lines, which wind around set pieces like the Moroccan fountain, Chinese palm trees and a giant black octopus from Tokyo, Japan to be explored by children. The green park has rolling hills, trees and plants suitable for picnics, sports (chess, table tennis, basketball, skating, boxing, working out etc.) and walking the d
notes: The apartment is suitable for kids from the age of 6, but it is not possible to choose that age-range in the setup. The apartment is on 4th floor. There is a 32" TV in the living room with no cable. But it has a Chromecast connected which means if you subscribe to Netflix, HBO etc. you can cast content from these streaming services to the TV via your phone/tablet/computer.  Tuesdays every other week - uneven weeks - there is municipal cleaning coming. The time differs but it is usually between 10am-2pm.
transit: The apartment is very close to Nørrebro Station where you can take the train or the bus, and it is quite easy to get around. We suggest that you use G-Maps when you have decided on a destination and make an itinerary since it is the easiest way to get the best and quickest connections. If you like walking it is also a nice way to see the city and for instance it doesn't take too long to get to the center of the city - about 15 min. by bus.  Approximate time distance with public transportation/walking, to some of the most popular destinations in Copenhagen:  - The airport: 40 min. - Tivoli: 25 min.  - Bakken (another amusement park open in summertime: 40 min.  - The little mermaid: 40 min. - Runde Tårn (Round Tower): 20 min.  - Christiania: 40 min.  - Nyhavn: 30 min.  - Strøget: 25 min.  - Christiansborg Slot (Castle): 30 min.  - Copenhagen Zoo: 40 min.  - The National Museum: 30 min.
access: You are allowed acces to all parts of the apartment. However, we kindly ask that you don't open the closests and cabinets in the bedroom, extra room and living room. You are very welcome though to open all cupboards and drawers in the kitchen.

neighborhood_overview: The Mikado is located smack dab in the middle of Little Tokyo.  Amid the intense activity of Downtown Los Angeles' current development boom, the 132-year old community of Little Tokyo has emerged as one of L.A.'s coolest places to dine, shop, find entertainment, and live.   Charming, walkable and friendly, Little Tokyo is setting a new, more relaxing pace and invites everyone to experience its charm sometime soon. Visitors will find dozens of delectable food options, great bars, live performances, world-class museums, and shopping that is not only eclectic but also affordable. It is no wonder that new residents are moving into the area every day, and visitors in increasing numbers are discovering Little Tokyo's many hidden gems.

neighborhood_overview: PLEASE READ BEFORE BOOKING!!! You wanted a real LA experience right? THIS Neighborhood is GRITTY.  If you're easily offended by a little trash in the streets, furniture on the sidewalk, a couple homeless people, or ice cream trucks this place might not be for you.   The neighborhood is hustling & bustling... kids playing, families walking, people fixing their cars, junk trunks, street vendors, church worship, tamale ladies, people congregating after a long work day. On weekends it isn't uncommon to hear music coming from neighborhood celebrations.  It is SAFE to walk around at any time of the day.   Occasionally there is police activity such as helicopter/patrols.  Not as bad as it sounds, but Im giving you the all the info, so there are no surprises or miscommunications. Please consider this a disclaimer, as it is unfair to reflect things out of my control such as "neighborhood" in review ratings regarding location.
notes: PLEASE CONSIDER before booking!! 1. PARKING - Only STREET PARKING available which can be difficult. Located 2 blocks away is Shamrock pay by day lot (10-20).  2. NEIGHBORHOOD - You wanted a real LA experience right?  Well don't be surprised by furniture on the sidewalk, a couple homeless people, or ice cream trucks!  Not for the faint of heart... Located in one of  Downtown LA's most urban areas, specifically called "Pico-Union" Comparable to San Francisco's Tenderloin & Mission Blvd Districts.  It may be considered "Gritty"  but its rich in culture, local flavor & access to everything you want to do when visiting LA. See "The Neighborhood" section. 3. NOISE - this neighborhood is bustling, its not uncommon to hear mariachi music, quinceñeras, church worship, or live music.  If its an issue, I will do my best to help resolve the issue for you at the time. Ear plugs & Eye Masks provided upon request! We got you covered.

neighborhood_overview: With an iconic skyline towering over London, striking and dynamic architecture and a vibrant, cosmopolitan feel, Canary Wharf is firmly established as a first class shopping and leisure destination There are plenty of bars, pubs, restaurants, luxury stores to shop and a massive shopping mall.  Canary Wharf is a major business district located in Tower Hamlets, London. It is one of the United Kingdom's two main financial centres – along with the traditional City of London – and contains many of the UK's tallest buildings, including the second-tallest, One Canada Square

You can make your way to Greenwich and see the Observatory, the park and enjoy the Market at Cutty Sark. host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

When I travel I love meeting the locals, and as a Melbourne girl I'd love to tell you about the best places to eat, visit, cycle and see in our wonderful town. And I've lived in the area of our AirBnB for around 20 years and I've seen it change an awful lot. I can tell you some history and also let you in on some local secrets!
But when I travel myself, I can't go past (URL HIDDEN) experience in Tokyo Japan and I was sold. So now it's my time to share the love and I hope you love our small but quirky and gorgeous place...we love it so much and hope you do too!

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

I have added a lot of my local favorites spots to the guest Guidebook here on AirBnb! You will be steps away from super trendy Bedford Avenue. There are many great shops, restaurants, bars, cafes, etc. There are live music venues, theaters, comedy clubs, two great parks, city views. ALL of this is within a 10 minute walking radius. And when you want to go to Manhattan, you can jump on the train and be there in minutes. You can be in the East Village, West Village, Soho, and other cool neighborhoods faster from here than many hotels in Manhattan.... Or, you can jump on a CitiBike and ride across the Williamsburg Bridge!
notes: The place is my home so all guests are expected to treat it with respect. Also, the building is small and the neighbors are kind and quiet. So please respect them as well.

access: You have access to my apartment only. There is NO ACCESS to backyard, basement, or roof.

He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: GREAT neighborhood, like a central hub to central LA.  Yet we have absolutely privacy and peace here.  We consider this area paradise  to live in with good reason. Entertainment industry executive heavy, musicians, writers, artists, celebrities, stars, and we are surrounded by incredible flora and fauna, mountains and vistas. The property itself is a huge cactus garden, with a view of the Hollywood sign at the top.  We are 5 minutes from Universal studio and the new Harry Potter attraction, a short walk to Runyon Canyon. Hikers paradise  -- you can walk out the door and start hiking, we are 5 minutes from Hollywood, Studio City, Burbank, Mullholand Drive, Beachwood Canyon, Laurel Canyon (about 10 minutes), Burbank, Warner Brothers and other studios. 40 minutes from Beaches. Starbucks is a short walk down the hill, as well as a great local Japanese restaurant, a new sandwich/salad/juice shop and other amenities.  Other eateries within walking distance -- Mercado, Breakroom Cafe, Tokyo F
notes: I have two tiny little dogs that live upstairs! They love people and other dogs and they will love you!  They may bark to greet you but after we've met, you're their new best friend. They are great guard dogs, and the area is really safe nonetheless, it's nice to have them be so alert! The garage is my artist's studio. We live in a creative thriving environment. Please see neighborhood notes below for restaurant suggestions. Please note that there will be a pet fee charged, particularly for longer stays.
transit: Many people use Uber and Lyft very easily. There's a bus stop 1/4 mile away. You can walk to eateries, and Cahuenga Boulevard West. There are stairs down to Adina Drive/Oakshire and also toward Cahuenga. Red line metro is 5 minute drive and park at Universal City. I have off -street parking for you in large front driveway There is more street parking on Woodrow Wilson Drive. As stated above - the locale is ultra central. I can't think of a better place then Cahuenga Pass for being right in the thick of it, yet not in the thick of it, all at once. I'm not sure how we've managed this, but it's true! Also to note: the traffic in our area is extremely light by LA standards. If you need to do errands in the Valley, it's a breeze. Driving in and around the hills is tranquil and beautiful. Very little congestion in the surrounding environs.
access: The entire apartment, patio outside the door to the left is exclusively yours,   4500 sq ft front yard. Private entrance to apartment.
interaction: I would be happy to help you with anything you need throughout your stay just ask! I will also respect your privacy unless you need something. Please do not hesitate to ask me for recommendations in the area. They are also listed here. ( under neighborhood notes)
house_rules: Please enjoy yourselves and be respectful of our neighbors.  The canyon is a unique audial experience. The apartment itself quiet inside, and you have very minimal noise throughout your stay, however outside sound travels throughout the canyon somewhat like an amphitheater so we keep our voices out of " shouting" version outside! Additinal note -- I am a pianist - classically trained, and learning jazz, theroy etc.  You may get the occasional classical concert, and the more plodding jazz practice. If I know your schedule somewhat I will try to practice when you are not home.  Please let me know i its a disturbance and I am happy to work around it. I don't practice all the time. Please park in the driveway/front area Some house rules are: please use cutting boards ONLY on the butcher's block counters in the kitchen.. They are totally new and my pride and joy.  No cutting etc, and just use the cutting boards that are provided and they will remain gorgeous for a long time! --NO SMOKING An

neighborhood_overview: Located on the main street of St. Kilda, you can access the famous suburbs' popular bars, restaurants and cafes at your convenience. Alternatively if you'd prefer to cook, there is a fully equipped kitchen and you can stock up on your groceries from the large supermarket 2 minutes walk away. This apartment is so central and convenient that you can take a stroll down to the beach, go for a run in the parklands or take a short 10 minute tram ride into Melbourne CBD. About St.Kilda Just 6km from Mebourne's city centre, St Kilda is known as Melbourne’s seaside playground and is much-loved by residents and visitors.  St Kilda is renowned for its expansive view of Port Phillip, safe sandy beach, palm-lined boardwalk, huge range of beach activities, big skies, gorgeous sunsets, parks and gardens, great restaurants, bars and cafés, fabulous old buildings, and its colourful past and present. St Kilda is home to many of Melbourne’s famous visitor attractions including Luna Park, the Esplanade Ho

transit: One secure car park available upon request (no extra cost). 2 minute walk to tram/light rail access (route 96).  10 minute walk to the beach.  15 minute taxi/uber ride into Melbourne CBD. neighborhood_overview: We live in a quaint friendly neighborhood! It's not "hipsterville" or super trendy, but it's super safe, and I love it!  You will often see kids playing in the streets all day on the weekends, but for the most part it's pretty quiet.  We're not in the hub of things, but we are only 10 - 15 minute drive away from all things exciting in Nashville!
notes: We have two dogs that are permanent fixtures at the house, and one that comes and goes with my boyfriend on occasion. Our dogs are super well behaved and very sweet. Junior (the pup) is very friendly and loving. Sasha is a cuddle bug, and if you let her, will curl up in your lap like a baby and live there....forever. Haha! Red (the boyfriend's dog) does his own thing when he comes over. He's very sweet, but normally not interested in much, and just sleeps in my room. They  spend most of their time wherever I happen to be in the house, but they do like to say hello to our guests if they hear you in a common area. You must love dogs if you plan on staying here!  Everyone always loves our dogs, and are really impressed by how well behaved they are. We run a tight doggy ship here. :)) Also, please note that we do have another room that we rent out. So there's a good chance that there are other guests in the house. It never seems to be an issue, as everyone is normally off enjoying Nashvill
transit: If you do not have a vehicle, we have public transportation that picks up right on our street. It's only about a 10 - 15 Uber or Lyft ride to East Nashville, Downtown, West End, etc (all of the places worth going)! Otherwise, we are about 10 - 15 minutes away from everywhere you need to go in the city! It's quite convenient!
access: The kitchen, laundry room, bathroom, front and back yard.
interaction: Our home is a bright, positive, and creative atmosphere. I have an art studio in the extra room, so I will most often be working in there or outside painting or working on my latest project. My boyfriend, Paul, drops in frequently, but is not a permanent fixture in my home. He is very personable and friendly, and will most likely want to talk with you about his farming and Monolithic Domes, if you're interested. :) I am very busy for the most part, but I am always available if you need me. You can call or text me for anything at all throughout the day if I'm not around. When I am at home, I always enjoy interacting with my guests if they're willing! Most of all, I will insure that you have a positive and fun experience staying at my place!
house_rules: I am pretty laid back. All I ask is that you're respectful of my place, and if you're coming in ultra late that you're respectful and conscious of the amount of noise you make.  Other than that, please make yourselves at home!
host_about:
I am a free spirited artist with a strong sense of self.  I dream big and pursue without doubt.  I love to laugh and I try not to take myself or tough situations too seriously. I'm passionate about everything I do, and try to surround myself with equally passionate people. 

I'm incredibly laid back, but I'm also very outgoing and social. I love being around people. I have traveled to most major cities in the US, and very few out of the country. However, I am ready to see the world! My dream destination is Tokyo, Japan, amongst many others. 

I love hosting and meeting new people while sharing and learning about their experiences and lives. As a host, I share my space openly and create a fun and positive environment for my guests. Everyone feels at home, and most feel as if we've known each other for a lifetime. As a guest, I am respectful, clean, interactive, cheerful and always grateful!

My motto in life is, "She who dares, wins!"

SELF CHECK-IN:  For your convenience and privacy this is a self-catering unit. It is your responsibility to find the place. host_about:
Nice to meet you.  My name is Will.  I love hosting on airbnb and it is my life.  It is tons of fun and there are new surprises every day!  I have met so many interesting people as a host and I look forward to those I will meet in the future.  

I am a sports fan, reader, movie goer, and I like to try new things.  I play golf, basketball, and just about any sport you can think of.  I love ramen, yakiniku, yakitori, and shabu shabu here in Japan.   I love to try pizza all over the world when I travel.   

Relationships are the most important thing for me in my personal life as well as business.  I like to go out and have a good time with my friends and meet new people.  

I have learned so much from my over three years as an airbnb host and I am pleased to say I have most questions answered for you before you ask them, whether it be in the description of the listing or in the detail I supply you with at confirmation.  Still, I am always thinking of ways to make the guest experience more comfortable, efficient, and hassle free.   This is my goal as a host.  I will continue to get more places every month so I can host more travelers.  I want everyone to see Tokyo at least once!   

Tokyo is a great place to come and people from all over the world visit here making it a truly international city.  I love Tokyo and seeing the amazing sights and people.  It is a great place to explore and every day can be different.  This is an awesome destination for walkers and wanders filled with friendly people, tasty restaurants, and plenty of lights.   My tip is to make the initial contact with Japanese people because they are typically shy at first.   They will be happy to try to practice their English with you.

Hope I can host you soon!  May your trip to Tokyo be as amazing as my 7 years here has been!

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

I am also permanent traveler more than 10 years, Visited more than 50 countries and 300 places. 
'NO TRAVEL NO LIFE' is my policy.

日本人です。香港と東京(新宿)の二箇所に拠点を構えていますが、事実上香港に居住し働いています。香港80%、日本20%くらいの頻度で行き来しております。私のAirbnbはこの香港と東京の自宅を貸し出してます(東京は私が不在中に貸し出す形です)。
香港には2015年の1月から6月まで度々訪れていました。この期間、自分自身が10箇所以上の香港のAirbnbを利用し、Airbnbユーザーにとって何が必要か、何が不必要かを分析し、香港の部屋を造りました。東京の部屋は、香港と東京を行き来しながら、不必要なものを処分し、できるだけ快適にすごせるように整えたつもりです。
また商用渡航と観光渡航共に10年以上、世界50カ国以上延べ300箇所以上を訪れています。
「NO TRAVEL NO LIFE」、これが私のモットーです。

neighborhood_overview: The Canary Wharf area is traditionally known to be the beating heart of London’s financial sector, full of tall buildings housing international banks. In recent years though, a large number of restaurants and bars have popped up in the area (and would be an easy 15-20 minute walk from the flat), such as Obica, Iberica, and Royal China. I particularly like Chai Ki, a modern Indian restaurant. You can also get drinks or have afternoon tea at the lovely Radisson Blu hotel nearby the apartment complex, which is a great setting to meet friends. Or, you can just use the kitchen in the apartment to cook yourself a meal and enjoy a nice comfy stay. With an iconic skyline towering over London, striking and dynamic architecture and a vibrant, cosmopolitan feel, Canary Wharf is firmly established as a first class shopping and leisure destination There are plenty of bars, pubs, restaurants, luxury stores to shop and a massive shopping mall. host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: The Canary Wharf area is traditionally known to be the beating heart of London’s financial sector, full of tall buildings housing international banks. In recent years though, a large number of restaurants and bars have popped up in the area (and would be an easy 15-20 minute walk from the flat), such as Obica, Iberica, and Royal China. I particularly like Chai Ki, a modern Indian restaurant. You can also get drinks or have afternoon tea at the lovely Radisson Blu hotel nearby the apartment complex, which is a great setting to meet friends. Or, you can just use the kitchen in the apartment to cook yourself a meal and enjoy a nice comfy stay. With an iconic skyline towering over London, striking and dynamic architecture and a vibrant, cosmopolitan feel, Canary Wharf is firmly established as a first class shopping and leisure destination There are plenty of bars, pubs, restaurants, luxury stores to shop and a massive shopping mall. host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in the neighborhood of Banker's Hill, which is located in central San Diego between the Gaslamp District and Hillcrest. It is a pedestrian friendly neighborhood.  Even though it is only one block away from Balboa Park, it has all the benefits of urban living. There are several convenience stores and smaller markets close by. Supermarkets and pharmacies are within a mile radius of the apartment.  There is a nice selection of coffee shops, cafes and restaurants within walking distance of the apartment. Enjoy great night life, fine dining and shopping whether you head one mile south to the Gaslamp District or one mile north to Hillcrest.  Balboa Park is just one block east of the apartment where you will find the San Diego Zoo, a variety of museums, hiking trails, and bike paths.  Seaworld and the beaches are about 15 minutes away by car.
notes: The unit is located on the 2nd floor and is not handicap accessible. No pets are allowed please. Check in time is 3 pm and check out is 11 am.  Flexibility is possible depending on the timing.  Please understand that we may not be very flexible when guests are checking out and checking in on the same day because it takes time to clean the apartment.  The rate for the apartment is final.
transit: The apartment does not have off street parking but there is metered street parking in the surrounding areas and free street parking a block away by Balboa Park.  The unit is about a 10 minute drive from the airport.  Taxis, Lyft, and Uber services are usually only a few minutes away.  Bus lines travel uptown to Hillcrest and downtown to the Gaslamp District.  Access to Amtrak and the San Diego Trolley is located downtown.
access: You will have access to the entire apartment.
interaction: The guests will have the entire apartment with no interaction with the host.

I went back to college to pursue a second career as an interior designer. I design each of my Airbnb units as if it is my own home.

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

summary: Hi! I have a very big and bright room in an 'altbau' in Schöneberg, bordering Kreuzberg in Berlin. It is super central, 5 minutes away from 4 main underground lines and walking distance to 2 great parks. You can get anywhere in Berlin in at most 30 minutes.
space: The room is very large and dynamic, with a few different areas, it's almost like a studio apartment within an apartment! There is a 'cozy corner' with nice lighting and a couch and carpet and some cool 'coffee table books' so it's the perfect space for chilling with a cup of tea and a book or curling up to watch a movie. There is a nice long work table facing the window which is perfect for drawing, writing and of course e-mailing. host_about:
Hey there! Im Sarah, a jewelry, fashion, textile designer/artist originally from  Richmond, Virginia. I have been living in Berlin for the last 6.5 years now, Holy MolY! 3.5 of those years have been spent here in this lovely flat in Schoeneberg, one of the coolest areas of Berlin (alright, they are ALL cool). But recently i have been falling more and more in love with this area, as it is such a mix of people and ages and backgrounds and more and more galleries and cafes are popping up close by, but it doesn't have the same trendy, fast changeability of Neukolln or even Kreuzberg. It is consistant and sure of itself...like me...? Haha, maybe its rubbing off a little bit :D Anyway, I live here with my two roommates, one of which is my best friend and the other is Reinhardt, a German man in his 60s who loves to watch football and a good deal at Aldi. He is very sweet and keeps to himself mostly, or just isn't home.

Aside from an artists/designer I am an English teacher and avid traveler. I was lucky enough to go on a sort of world tour last year, starting with NY and ending with Tokyo, with SF and SD and S.K somewhere in the middle. I absolutely fell in love with Japan (Kyoto/Osaka and Tokyo) and MUST get back there to spend some real time there...like a year!

I love to eat, drink, laugh, dance and create and certainly love to meet people from all over, building those connections that are so important to our SouL!

Amid the intense activity of Downtown Los Angeles' current development boom, the 132-year old community of Little Tokyo has emerged as one of L.A.'s coolest places to dine, shop, find entertainment, and live.   Charming, walkable and friendly, Little Tokyo is setting a new, more relaxing pace and invites everyone to experience its charm sometime soon. Visitors will find dozens of delectable food options, great bars, live performances, world-class museums, and shopping that is not only eclectic but also affordable. It is no wonder that new residents are moving into the area every day, and visitors in increasing numbers are discovering Little Tokyo's many hidden gems.

neighborhood_overview: On your door step it's eclectic: from a "greasy spoon" English breakfast cafe to a smart Italian restaurant, from Japanese and Korean food to a laid back cocktail bar - either end of the main street is a train station. During the day it's buzzing, the locals mix with a lot of creatives (advertising agencies and record labels are based in the area) and bankers (you can see the financial district and skyscrapers if you go up to the top floor of the building). Research the area online. East is different to west London where you'll find Big Ben, Covent Garden etc - although they are 15 mins on the tube from the flat. It has more housing blocks, it's more built up. The building: it used to be a cinema and film studio and is attached to a famous boxing hall and swimming pool... with a hotel covered in artistic metal next to it - it's as random and weird as the area itself. Not ideal for families, young children or those looking for a very quiet part of London.
notes: Do your research before you choose this area. Whilst my apartment is certainly in and around central London, it is far removed from common perceptions of London. This is the east-end: it's old looking but full of young people, it's colourful, it can be noisy, it may even seem chaotic, it's definitely very busy and bustling. What's it not is the west-end, so if you're looking for the London you see in films, the east-end is probably not for you.
transit: 1 min walk to Bethnal Green station, Holborn/Oxford Circus/Leicester Sq a few stops away. 24-hour buses next to the station. You can rent a bike with your credit card from the docks outside the building.

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: Your hosts made Madison Valley their home when settling in Seattle 5 years ago... and haven't looked back since. We love walking the streets of this neighborhood, and we will gladly suggest fun walks depending on your interests. Stroll to the beach at Madison Park. Walk by multi-million dollar estates. Discover hidden neighborhood gems such as the farmhouse with horses in the yard and the home that doubles as an eclectic art studio and antique truck gallery. Take a walk through the fabled Arboretum to Lake Washington. Once you have worked up your appetite, enjoy the countless restaurants that Madison Valley ("Little Paris") has to offer. In addition to French gems, try our favorite tapas restaurant or the best Japanese food east of Tokyo. Take your morning coffee in one of numerous bakeries. Or opt for Thai, pan-Asian, craft pizza, Tex-Mex or more. Our home provides easy access to Downtown (Pikes Place Market, Seattle Art Museum, Seattle Great Wheel), Seattle Center (Space Needle, Chih

(In fact, the other 3 units in this 4-unit building combine to provide flexible options to accommodate up to 20.) Under the "Listings" header, click on "view all listings." transit: We live a few short blocks from bus lines that will take you to Seattle's numerous neighborhoods (Madison Park, Capitol Hill, Downtown, Belltown, Seattle Center, South Lake Union). Queen Anne, Ballard, and Fremont are more easily accessed by car. Our home offers garage parking for one car. Street parking for additional cars is plentiful and free.
host_about: My wife and I are world travelers.  We've traveled to ~60 countries around the world... on all 7 continents!  While we enjoy a fancy hotel now and then, nothing beats the comforts of a real HOME away from home.  Having rented countless vacation homes during our time, we have copious notes of what we do and don't like.  We aspire to make our Airbnb rental home an example of all the best traits we have found in our vacation rentals.

はじめましてティムです。7年間日本住んでことあります。私の日本語は完璧でわないですがコミュニケーション問題ないです。私の奥さんAchikoは宮城県に生まれ、17年間東京に住んでいました。ハピターン250%と無印良品が大好きです。(ハッピーターンパウダー中毒は2015年暮れに卒業。私はラーメン中毒です。)

私たちの家の近所面白いよ。地ビール工場二つありレストランいっぱい、お土産屋、バス停近い、4ドル映画館あります。

バス停から家まで全然安全です。女性一人大丈夫。前のゲストのレビューを読んで下さい。

【ご宿泊を検討中の方へ】
最近過度なホスティングを期待する日本人ゲストが多くいらっしゃいます。日本ではAirbnbの概念が他国とは違った理解をされてるように感じます。Airbnbはホテルやホストファミリーではありません。もし快適なサービスやケアを受けたいのならホテルに宿泊されることをお勧めします。私達はホテルマンやガイド的なサービスはしておりません。例えば、ご自分で調べようとせず『2人に聞けばいいか』という考えは非常に困ります。私達に頼らずご自分の力で行動してください。部屋にはオリジナルガイドや沢山の本を用意してますしポートランドは旅行者にとても優しい町です。
 また宿泊されるのは一般住宅、つまり私達の日常生活の中に滞在していただくことになります。ハウスルールは私達の穏やかな暮らしを守るためにこれまでの経験を基に決めてます。これを尊重し同意いただける方のみ予約を受入れております。私達もゲストとそのプライバシーを尊重しています。
 最後に、予約リクエストをお送りいただいた際にプロフィールや自己紹介がない方はお断りしております。もしあなたなら、どんな人で、何処から、何の為に来たか知らない人を自分の家に泊めることができますか?短くても結構なのでポートランドに来る理由や好きな事を書いてリクエストください。
※フェイスブックのページもあります。是非見て私達についてもっと知ってください。「ポートランド日本語OKのAirbnb」

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: It is a relatively quiet residential neighborhood with a lot of park space and trees between buildings. The style of the buildings is quite unique as they where build as a complex during the 60's with the aesthetics of that time. While walking around you will see interesting ways the residents have used to modify their spaces with small gardens in front of the ground floor apartments or added balconies on higher ones. There is a sense of old style neighborhood with residents spending time at the parks or local cafes and restaurants in the evenings or chatting at the streets and I find early evenings hours there quite picturesque with the tram passing through.  The farmers' market there every Saturday is quite large and very cheap so I recommend you to visit it for shopping or for just watching some interesting friendly characters selling their products there. It runs cross and by the tram lines and it finishes around 15:00 so you can get the best prices just before then.
transit: For nightlife. you can visit the cafes and some restaurants on the way to the metro or you can easily take the metro to go anywhere. If you don't feel like commuting and you don't mind walking a bit, in 20 min you can be at the busier Koukaki area where there are many more cafes and restaurants. One of the busiest parts of it is right outside Sygrou-Fix metro station. Of course you can also ride the metro for one stop to go there. I usually just walk.   You can even walk to the old town Plaka or the Acropolis if you don't want to use the train. You can reach the Acropolis in 30 min (walk) and you can enter Plaka in 25 min. By metro that can be much shorter as two stops from Neos Kosmos to the Acropolis station take less than 5 min.  For art lovers, you can walk in 7 min to the National Museum of Contemporary Art and 5 min to the Onassis Cultural Center. Please (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) them. The Acropolis museum is also in less than 30 min walking distance.
access: My space is very conveniently located for exploring Athens and for even going to the beach as the tram (5 min walk to the tram stop) can take you to the nearest Athenian beaches. Coming from the airport or the Piraeus port isn't complicated. From the airport you only need to change train once at "Syntagma" station, take the red line towards "Ellinikon" and get off at "Neos Kosmos" station which is only 7 min walk away from the apartment. From Piraeus port you change trains at "Omonia" station to the red line again towards "Ellinikon" and get off at "Neos Kosmos" station again. From the port it is also easy and much faster to get a taxi as highways connect it to Syngrou avenue from where you can directly turn in to my street.
interaction: We will be happy to help with any extra information you need upon arrival and we will also be available to offer any other help during your stay. You can contact us via email or over the phone.

neighborhood_overview: Known as "Little Taipei" in the 1980's, Downtown Monterey Park (along Garvey Avenue) contains many Chinese businesses and restaurants. These authentic restaurants are often viewed as Monterey Park's biggest claim to fame. Like South Bay area in relation to Little Tokyo, Monterey Park and the surrounding San Gabriel Valley area (plus Rowland Heights further east on the 60 freeway) is the new residential heart of the Chinese community in Los Angeles. While ethnic Chinese represents more than half of the city's population, incredible diversity exists in the city. Monterey Park is home to families who trace their roots to places as different as Mexico, Taiwan, Hong Kong, China, Japan, Vietnam, Thailand and Indonesia. Monterey Park - Asian-American friendly, All-American, and 100% Angeleno!
notes: A coin-operated washer is located in the laundry room next to the carport. The cost is 1.75/wash. There is a drying rack inside the unit which works well due to the low humidity climate in Los Angeles.  The open space parking is good for compact car only. For and full size and above vehicles, please utilize the street parking. For street parking, do keep in mind no parking on Wednesday form 8:00 am to 12:00 pm on the property side of Hathaway Ave. The street across the property belongs to City of Alhambra, no overnight parking without a permit.

Thank you for your cooperation!

neighborhood_overview: Dalston This is one of the most hippest creative parts of London with new bars and eateries opening almost every week. Pop up shops, vintage shops, a fab art house cinema, a coffee shop that was selected as the coolest coffee shop in London by the New York Times is at the end of our street.  There are many excellent Turkish restaurants, an amazing Indian restaurant, a local pub that serves real British ale and thai food. Check out our air bnb guidebook for many local and nearby suggestions, there is a huge choice. All within easy walking distance Stoke Newington A bit longer to walk but still pretty accessible is vibrant and alternative with many more independent shops and eateries  You will not find the likes of McDonalds here for example. There is an amazing cemetery you can walk through (in the daytime!) should you want an interesting walk. Then there is Clissold Park which on a sunny day will have swarms of locals picnicking or just chilling out.  Newington Green Is a short walk wh
notes: Price listed is for two people we can accommodate up to two extra people with comfy mattresses stored in the apartment, these are normally stored under the main bed and can be placed in lounge..  Our properties tend to book out quickly so bear in mind to book as expediently as your circumstances allow. We are flexible over check in and out times but we do like to prepare properties to ensure everything is in order so whilst flexible we do expect guests to be co-operative and flexible themselves. This may mean checking out and we storing luggage if need be. Any questions... Just ask!
transit: It is important to remember and know that London is a huge city and that no one place is close to all the attractions and shopping that London has to offer. If you want to be staying next door to Buckingham Palace then we like 99.9% of properties in London are not next door to Buckingham Palace and equally if you got that close to our Royal Palaces you would be paying a fortune in airbnb rental costs!.  We also get asked sometimes; 'Are you close to the city centre where all traditional attractions are?  The answer is; no one place in London is close to all the attractions because they are spread around London. You will have to use the transport system to get around and the transport system in London is one of the best in the world, we are well sited as a launchpad to visit most areas of london and of course have our own unique scene on the doorstep. To go to Buckingham Palace and many of the more traditional attractions you will need to commute....  So bus, tube, overground train, tax

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

Hi, I'm Richard. 25 years ago, I opened a very popular little Japanese restaurant in London's Chinatown called Tokyo Diner.  Although I no longer work on the Front Desk, I'm still the owner - so I interview all the staff (in Japanese) and I taste everything on the menu.

My flat is just the other side of Chinatown and I have a couple of extra bedrooms which are needed when chefs and other visitors come over from Japan. However, those rooms are empty for most of the time, so that's why I have decided to start using Airbnb.

My motto is "clean living, fun loving". I have always liked to exercise in the parks (just four minutes away) and, in the last couple of years, I have been completely taken over by Swing dancing (Lindyhop, Blues, Balboa). There is a real explosion of Swing in London at the moment and I usually go dancing five or six nights a week - so it's really convenient that I live in the centre of town!

neighborhood_overview: IMPORTANT!!  Not for the faint of heart...  Located in one of  Downtown LA's most urban neighborhoods called "Pico-Union" Comparable to San Francisco's Tenderloin & Mission Blvd Districts.  It may be considered "Gritty" but its rich in culture, local flavor & access to everything you want to do when visiting LA.    The neighborhood is hustling & bustling... kids playing, families walking, people fixing their cars, junk trunks, furniture on the sidewalks, a couple harmless homeless guys, church worship, ice cream trucks, tamale ladies in the morning, people congregating after a long work day. During weekends it isn't  uncommon to hear mariachi or latin music coming from quinceñeras, birthday parties, baby showers. Occasionally there is police activity such as helicopter/patrols.  Not as bad as it sounds, but Im giving you the all the info, so there are no surprises or miscommunications.
notes: PLEASE REVIEW Carefully before booking!! Things to Consider:   1. PARKING - Only STREET PARKING available which can be difficult. Located 1 block away is a parking lot where day & short term passes can be purchased. 2. NOISE - this neighborhood is bustling, its not uncommon to hear mariachi music, quinceñeras, church worship, or live music.  If its an issue, I will do my best to help resolve the issue for you at the time. Ear plugs & Eye Masks provided upon request! We got you covered. 3. SURROUNDINGS - You wanted a real LA experience right?  Well don't be surprised by furniture on the sidewalk, a couple homeless people, or ice cream trucks!
transit: Conveniently located!! Minutes to (WALK): 5 mins - Staples Center, Microsoft Theater, Grammy Museum, LA Live, Loyola Law School, Regal Cinema, Yard house, Toms Urban, Metro Bus Stop 7 mins - Convention Center, K-town 10 mins - Target, H& M, Gold's Gym, Fig & 7th, Metro Station 15 mins - FiDM, Exchange, Main Street, Pershing Square, Mayan (DRIVE) 1 min - 110 & 10 fwys 8-10 mins - USC, Coliseum, Arts District, Chinatown, Union Station 10-15 mins Little Tokyo, 5 & 101 fwys 15-20 mins - Hollywood, USC Medical Center, Alhambra, Rosemead 30 mins to LAX UBER - First Ride up to 20 is on me! download app use promo code: 1ja7k LYFT - first ride credit of 50  promo code: grab50 update 4/2016: lyft and uber now can pick up from LAX!! If you would like info about a specific location, please just ask!
access: You will have access to entire premises, gated entrance, on-site laundry, back area access (to smoke), front balcony for urban sunsets or front stoop to sit & people watch.
interaction: You're in luck...Whether you need me or not, Im reachable 24/7, via text, or email. Need suggestions or recommendations for local activities and sights? Im here to help.  Also friendly neighbors, just ask!  We welcome: - Our International brothers & sisters from Europe, Japan, Taiwan, Australia, New Zealand & South America!!
house_rules: - No cigarette smoking inside - Please be considerate when bringing over more then 3 guests. - Report any problems you experience (i.e. plumbing, noise) - Have Fun - Ask me anything - Be Safe - Treat the place as if it were you mothers. We love pets but unfortunately we'd prefer if you didn't bring them.

neighborhood_overview: Here is a great description of the neighborhood provided by AirBNB: https://www.airbnb.com/locations/san-francisco/the-castro The home is located just a short 5 minute walk to the Castro District — with lots of restaurants, cafes (including Starbucks), bars, supermarkets, and the MUNI underground / bus / streetcar station. It is also located only minutes away from Corona Heights Park — with tennis courts, a basketball court, a good hiking trail and stunning views of the city! Here are distances to other notable places nearby: Haight-Ashbury: 19 minutes by foot / 4 minutes drive Mission/Dolores Park:  18 minutes by foot / 5 minute drive Golden Gate Park: 25 minutes by foot / 6 minute drive Hayes Valley: 30 minutes by foot / 13 minute drive Union Square: 1 hour by foot / 22 minute drive Nearest Supermarket: 7 minutes by foot / 2 minute drive SFO Airport: 25 minute drive
notes: San Francisco Short-Term Rental Permit: STR-(PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN) Please keep in mind that you will be staying in a home, not a hotel. Therefore, I ask that you treat the space with the same respect you would show if it was your own.  Indoor and outdoor speakers are provided for your music enjoyment, but I ask that you keep speaker volumes to a reasonable level so as not to disturb the neighbors.  My home has a keyless electronic lock and you will be provided with the entry code upon check-in. The house is on a hill. If you don't mind a brief climb, you'll love the proximity to everything the city has to offer. I have an adorable Coton De Tulear dog who is hypoallergenic, quiet, and very friendly. If you love dogs, you will fall in love with him! Check out the reviews from my other listing as it is the same house -- this listing is just for the upstairs, while the other listing includes downstairs as well.
transit: The house comes with a driveway parking spot, so you don’t have to worry about street parking! The MUNI underground is only a 5 minute walk, which will take you to the downtown shopping district in only 6 minutes. In the same spot, you can find above ground busses and street cars.  Apart from driving and public transport, San Francisco has literally thousands of Uber and Lyft drivers and it is never more than about a 5 minute wait to have a car pull up at the front door. Walking in the area is safe and provides a great way to see the area — in addition to being good exercise!
access: You will have exclusive access to the main floor AND garden of Bali Hai Castro with your own door entry code.
interaction: I love learning all about my guests and welcome company. However, if you prefer privacy I am more than happy to accommodate you in that way as well. I will be staying in the lower-level suite (with its own entrance from the street) along with Dexter, my medium sized, well behaved, hypoallergenic, and quiet dog (trust me, you will fall in love!). I am a long-time San Francisco resident and can give you great advice about sight-seeing spots and restaurants -- or answer other questions that you may have.
house_rules: Please note that since this is an Asian inspired house -- and in order to keep the home as clean as possible for your stay, there is a no shoe policy inside the house. House slippers are provided for all guests.
host_about:
Hi! 

I’ve lived in San Francisco for 21 years now, prior to which I lived in Asia (Tokyo, Japan to be specific). I also consider myself a citizen of the world, as I have traveled to 49 countries so far and in addition to English, speak some Japanese and French. 

In my travels, I have stayed at some amazing places and know what a difference great hospitality can make to a trip. I therefore strive to create an experience at Bali Hai Castro that will be memorable and unique. My aim is that you will come back each time you return to San Francisco to stay here agin. 

I know the city and surrounding area very well and am always happy to give suggestions to make your stay exceptional. I am also a foodie and am working on a type of food blog — so if you are looking for great restaurants, I can share with you my favorites.

As a guest, I am responsible, trustworthy, and neat. Being a host myself, I can completely put myself in your shoes and am very respectful of your space. I love AirBNB because it really affords one the opportunity to live like a local when you travel to a new area.

In my free time, I enjoy spending time with my puppy (Dexter), working out, hiking, traveling, skiing, and generally making the most of life. 

If you are considering booking my home, I know you will love your stay here!

If I have made a reservation request with you, I can promise that you will be delighted to have me as a guest.

Hope to meet you soon,

Laurence
