name: Zen Fairyland Rainbows Room
summary: Just 10 minutes by bus from Sydney's Central station, in a kind of retro Sesame-Street. It is an enclave of peace, green & good people.   High ceilings, high ideals, and Japanese levels of thoughtfulness.
space: This home is for people who are busy changing the world, or at least their part of it, and need a leafy green re-charge, right here.  The house has an airy, high-ceilinged dinging room, a ballroom really.  Three chickens roam the garden, and give you an egg for breakfast. Gilmore the cute cat might give you cuddles. All this peacefulness is just 10 minutes to Sydney Central Station. Your room is by the front verandah, a lovely place to sit behind the curtain of green plants, and have a dappled-sunshine breakfast.  I've upgraded the bed from the one in the photo, you now get to sleep in 'The Cloud Bed', a high Queen bed that makes sleeping one of life's great pleasures.  Our house is semi-Japanese. That means, we aspire to be super-observant, doing the small things that matter. Like keeping your room crisp and restful, and making you happy. I usually have live-in assistants who help keep the place nice, and you looked after. We often do easy yoga in the evenings, and you will be invited

notes: Check in is from 4pm.  Earlier check-ins are usually possible, just ask and we will arrange something. I'm only able to accept guests with a clear photo and full profile, one that gives me a good sense of who they are, and why I'd love to host them. Do what works...profile.
transit: A constant stream of busses run down Parramatta road to the city, a 2-3 minute walk away.  It costs 30 - 40 to and from the airport by Uber, most days of the week.
access: You will have your own bedroom, and share a bathroom. We are tidy, thoughtful and yielding, and have become experts in the art of Bathroom-sharing.   There is a kitchen for your breakfast, we will make a shelf for you to store any food. Its possible to make dinner here too, if we make an arrangement before you book.
interaction: My levels of interaction are super-flexible.  Some guests like to retreat. I can respect that privacy, I lived in Japan.  Other guests and I get enthralled by each other, and have fun cooking and putting on dinner parties together.
house_rules: A great guest will: Keep sounds to a low-volume after 11pm Use thoughtful observation, and we will all be fine.
host_about:
I'm a permaculture designer and Illustrator, with a serious commitment to making my world luscious. So far, so good, thanks to the excellent people who come and stay in my house, and who let me into theirs, long before AirB&B.

I've  living and working part of each year in Australia, part in Tokyo, and little working trips all over the place.

I write a Magazine column in Japanese, 'Cecilia's Permacutlure Slow Life'. Its about creative ways to de-trap your life of wasted time, energy and affection, freeing you up to do the good work you were put on this world to do. 

For 9 years Ive run a share-house for creative people - you can read about it on my Blog Balcony Garden dreaming

My hobbies are Sado (Japanese tea eremony), balcony gardening, fancy dress parties, and drawing illustrations of the quirky world I would like to live in, and often actually do.  These are also my jobs.

Ive been a WWOOF host and traveler for many years (willing workers on organic farms). Even when my farm was just a balcony garden. 

I don't have a life motto exactly, but when thing go wrong, I ask myself 'Whiner or designer?', and that gets me positive and resourceful, finding a way to make things better.
If things go wrong for you I won't say it though. I'll just help where I can xx

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: Hammond Street is a hidden away street in Dublin 8. Some of the locals call it Blackpitts, some call it Warrenmount - it's full of local lore. The street is quiet and settled and the house is part of row of terrace cottages that is classic to Dublin. Nearby are friendly neighbours, some of Dublin's most popular breakfast spots and cafés, local pubs, an excellent market for organic food. Top sight-seeing destination St. Patrick's Cathedral is only steps away.  You'll be a 10-15-minute walk to town centre and temple bar and a 10-minute walk to lively Camden Street and its restaurants and live music venues (Whelan's). Grand Canal is very close for your morning run or for an afternoon picnic. If you're an antiques fan, head up to Francis Street to poke around on a Saturday afternoon. Blackpitts is charming, cozy and dynamic. It, along with The Liberties, The Tenters and The Coombe was part of the cIty's textile district and the neighbourhood is bursting with local history. notes: Other house perks include: -Board games (backgammon and Settlers of Catan) -Concierge cultural experiences: ask me for arts and culture recommendations or nightlife tips, only happy to oblige.

I am director of Dublin's most-loved and biggest interdisciplinary arts festival, Tiger Dublin Fringe, so you can be guaranteed that I'll give you some recommendations for theatre, dance, comedy, circus, gigs or galleries to go see - just let me know the kind of art experience you want and I'm happy to matchmake. Generally I only rent out my place when I'm out of town, but no fear, there's a key system that works and I'm always happy to reply to an SMS or a phone call.

host_about:
Hi my name is Kris.

I'm Canadian and live in Dublin, Ireland. I speak English and French (and a bit of Spanish and Japanese). I'm interested in neighbourhoods with an urban feel, places located in spots with locally owned shops and cafés - or beaches and parks. I'm Artistic Director and CEO of Dublin Fringe Festival - the city's largest interdisciplinary arts festival that sweeps across the city every September. It's amazing to get to know Dublin through its artists and happenings - the city's cultural calendar is always packed with great stuff.

I travel often, and always try to add a bit of exploring a city to a work trip. I'm social and friendly and like to have my own space to retreat to - when I travel I can be home late from a show and up early for a meeting. I usually travel with a suitcase and a decent budget, I haven't backpacked in a long time.  I love to discover new things about a place - like to live like the locals. If you're ever in Dublin- would be happy to share some favourite spots!

Can't live without: a great performing arts venue, festival and gallery, record collection, dinner and drinks with friends, good place for a drink, bike riding, a gym or place to go running, food of all kind. A bit of nightlife, gay or otherwise is a good thing too.

Favourite destinations: Madrid, Melbourne, Reykjavik, Cape Breton, Kyoto, Tokyo, Ljubljana, Rio de Janeiro, Ghent and San Francisco.

Hope to meet you soon.

Kris

My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: Camden has fast become one of London's trendiest and popular areas. It used to be an area which attracted old school rockers, but now there are so many more things to see and do here. It is a busy and bustling central London borough which is famed for it's international food market and artisan stalls at the Camden lock. Many independent retailers also choose this area to promote and sell their products. When you get here you will realise that this area is so popular with locals and tourists alike for good reason! Shoppers should rejoice!!! Camden will be the perfect place for you. Make sure you spend a few hours exploring the extensive Camden markets and the amazing conversion The Stables. You can find great deals here and all manner of things to buy. If you fancy experiencing a typical British pub then you are in luck as there are loads of great pubs in Camden. Chill at the Hawley Arms or The Lock Tavern; rock with the rockabillies at The Elephant's Head; kick on until way past your b
transit: The apartment is only a 2 minute walk from Camden Road overground station and 9 mins walk from Camden Town tube station. The tube station is serviced by the Northern line which will take you directly to Kings Cross station (great if you are travelling by train!), and other sights in London such as Leicester Square, the Houses of Parliament, and Waterloo station. There are also plenty of buses in the area, which are a great way of travelling if you like to have a peek at your surroundings as you travel. A great local tip is to download the Citymapper app. This free app will plan your journey for you efficiently and quickly. It gives you a variety of different transport options such as bike, rail, tube and Uber taxi. It will also take you step by step through your journey as you travel and notify you when you are nearing your destination.

notes: One important note: IF YOU ARE ALLERGIC TO DOG HAIR OR FIND DOGS "IMPURE" FOR RELIGIOUS REASONS, MY HOME MAY NOT BE RIGHT FOR YOUR:  WHEN IT IS NOT USED BY MY GUESTS, I AM CALLING THIS HOME FOR LUNA AND MYSELF, a German short haired pointer dog.  I do not share some people's belief that dogs are unhygienic in any way, at least not any more unhygienic than human being are...  Despite all efforts to thoroughly clean the flat as a preparation your check-in, if you look closely, you may be able to spot a few remaining dog hair. Hence the disclaimer here.

interaction: //  GOOD COMMUNICATION WITH MY GUESTS BEFORE THEIR ARRIVAL AND THE OPPORTUNITY TO MEET THEM IN PERSON IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT FOR ME AS A HOST! //  MY AIM IS TO GREET ALL OF MY GUESTS IN PERSON AND MEET THEM IN PERSON WHILE INVITING THEM FOR A WELCOME DRINK! house_rules: PLEASE RESPECT THE FOLLOWING HOUSE RULES: 1. TAKE OFF YOUR STREET SHOES IN THE ENTRANCE AREA IN THE FLAT, I am happy to provide comfortable 'house shoes' to wear inside. This will be a major contributions towards protecting the antique wooden parquet floor and reducing the noise level for my downstairs neighbors.  2. SMOKING IS NOT PERMITTED INSIDE, YOU CAN SMOKE ON BALCONIES. 3. BE RESPECTFUL TO MY NEIGHBORS AND PAY ATTENTION TO THE NOISE LEVEL, ESPECIALLY FROM 10PM - 8AM. That is especially important when you keep your windows open and when entering and leaving the building. If you want to party, go out and have a good time I am an easy going host but I cannot tolerate noise complaints! IMPORTANT NOTE: under my kitchen is my downstairs neighbor's bedroom. Noise travels more easily in an old house. I therefore recommend to use the living room when you want to sit together in the evening to have drinks.  Also, pay attention to your bags and suitcases if you are checking out early on a
host_about:
Hi there, I am George and proud to be AirBnB Superhost for the 10th time in a row! I love hosting people from all over the world. 
What I enjoyed most during my 18-month travel around the world a few years ago was to spend time with friends who were kind enough to host me in their homes (San Francisco, Tokyo, Miami, Rio de Janeiro just to name a few). Now that I have settled down in my favorite city Berlin, I love to return the  favor and open up my place to guests from other countries and cultures to make it their home away from home.
I am a gay man, currently living by myself  with my adorable dog Luna, a German short hair pointer after my longtime Brazilian partner from Rio de Janeiro moved out to start a degree in 'Fashion Branding'  @ Amsterdam Fashion Institute (AmFI). I have always enjoyed hosting other people, showing them my city and sharing with them my view of Berlin, what to do and how to make the most of their time. 
Professionally, I work as an business consultant for a big American company. As a balance for my creative half I like art (both visiting exhibitions as well as getting my own small eclectic collection), going for long walks with my dog in the country side around Berlin, architecture, traveling, enjoying the amazing cultural offers in Berlin ranging from opera to nights (and days) in my favorite club Berghain. But above all, I am  a huge fan of Franco-Belgian comics such as Tintin, Blake & Mortimer, Sopie & Starter etc. Not only do I collect these comics but I also collect art work such as Aroutcheff toys, cars and vehicles. 
The other passion is decorating my apartement with rare antiques and art work. It makes me proud that virtually anyone who comes to visit immediately falls in love with my flat. 
My favorite author is Haruki Murakami, about time he gets the Nobel prize for literature! Favorite destinations are Nepal, Japan and Easter Islands. 
If I am not busy enjoying the cultural attractions of Berlin, I love watching well made US series e.g. Sopranos, The Wire and Game of Thrones. 
Favorite directors are Pedro Almodovar, David Lynch, Jim Jarmusch and Francois Truffeaut. 
If you stay with me, you should not be afraid of dogs. I would like my guests to really feel at home at my place and invite them to the  entire space rather than just their room for cooking, relaxing, borrowing my books or taking a sun bath on one of my balconies. 
My leitmotiv is "Work hard & party hard" and "Live and let live", I am tolerant towards other views and opinions as long as they do the same. I hate intolerant and hypocritical people who think they have eaten the truth with a spoon. Gay and lesbian friendly!
street: Plänterwald, Berlin, Berlin 12435, Germany

neighborhood_overview: The Mikado is located smack dab in the middle of Little Tokyo.  Amid the intense activity of Downtown Los Angeles' current development boom, the 132-year old community of Little Tokyo has emerged as one of L.A.'s coolest places to dine, shop, find entertainment, and live.   Charming, walkable and friendly, Little Tokyo is setting a new, more relaxing pace and invites everyone to experience its charm sometime soon. Visitors will find dozens of delectable food options, great bars, live performances, world-class museums, and shopping that is not only eclectic but also affordable. It is no wonder that new residents are moving into the area every day, and visitors in increasing numbers are discovering Little Tokyo's many hidden gems.
transit: We recommend uber, lyft or taxi.  Local bus stops  Nearby Metro Stops  There is a metro stop 2 blocks away from the Mikado.  Union Station is 1 metro stop away. host_about:

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

Discover hidden neighborhood gems such as the farmhouse with horses in the yard and the home that doubles as an eclectic art studio and antique truck gallery. transit: We live a few short blocks from bus lines that will take you to Seattle's numerous neighborhoods (Madison Park, Capitol Hill, Downtown, Belltown, Seattle Center, South Lake Union). neighborhood_overview: Downtown LA is an up-and-coming part of LA and has a vibrant nightlife with lots of restaurants, bars, and clubs walking distance from the space. Little Tokyo is a 20-minute walk and LA Live / Staples Center is about a 30-minute walk. Across the street is the now-famous Little Damage ice cream shop (featured in a story about goth ice cream!).
notes: Loft has two skylights but no windows (loft is one of two in the center of the building). The tatami room is blocked off with Japanese screens, but there are no lockable doors to the "room." The loft itself has both a wooden door and a metal screen door and is quite secure. There is wifi but otherwise poor cellphone reception in the space, unless you have T-Mobile (there's a mini cell tower in the loft). I have a kitty that may be around, and I'll try to keep her out of your space (but I'm ok to share her with you!).
transit: Plenty of Ubers and Lyfts frequent my area. There's also a major train hub a few blocks away that now serves the Expo line, which goes to within a few blocks of Santa Monica pier (1.75!).
access: The restroom and kitchen are in the main part of the loft and you're welcome to use either as you like, including the fridge, stove, and oven. I also have a projector that you can probably use, though please ask me.
interaction: I'll probably be around but will mostly be in another part of the loft. I've lived in LA for almost five years and can give you recommendations on things to eat, see, and do in the general LA area. If I have time, I might also be able to play tour guide for you.
house_rules: No shoes on the tatami mats. Slippers will be provided for walking through the rest of the space. 420 friendly! Close restroom door before smoking. Quiet hours are after 11pm weekdays and 2pm weekends.

Anyway, hope you enjoy your stay if you decide to rent my room!

Known as "Little Taipei" in the 1980's, Downtown Monterey Park (along Garvey Avenue) contains many Chinese businesses and restaurants. These authentic restaurants are often viewed as Monterey Park's biggest claim to fame. Like South Bay area in relation to Little Tokyo, Monterey Park and the surrounding San Gabriel Valley area (plus Rowland Heights further east on the 60 freeway) is the new residential heart of the Chinese community in Los Angeles. While ethnic Chinese represents more than half of the city's population, incredible diversity exists in the city. Monterey Park is home to families who trace their roots to places as different as Mexico, Taiwan, Hong Kong, China, Japan, Vietnam, Thailand and Indonesia. Monterey Park - Asian-American friendly, All-American, and 100% Angeleno!

neighborhood_overview: The Mikado is located smack dab in the middle of Little Tokyo.  Amid the intense activity of Downtown Los Angeles' current development boom, the 132-year old community of Little Tokyo has emerged as one of L.A.'s coolest places to dine, shop, find entertainment, and live.   Charming, walkable and friendly, Little Tokyo is setting a new, more relaxing pace and invites everyone to experience its charm sometime soon. Visitors will find dozens of delectable food options, great bars, live performances, world-class museums, and shopping that is not only eclectic but also affordable. It is no wonder that new residents are moving into the area every day, and visitors in increasing numbers are discovering Little Tokyo's many hidden gems.

name: The Blue Room - Zen Fairyland
summary: This is the lucky room...you get to stay when we are between permanent housemates, in this extraordinary, creative household. Its got western looks, a Japanese spirit, and its only 10 minutes bus and walk to Central Station.
space: This home is for people who are busy changing the world, or at least their part of it, and need a leafy green re-charge, right here.  The house has an airy, cathedral-ceilinged dining and lounge room, a ballroom really, surrounded by forest-like green. Your room is fully furnished, with a queen size bed nicknamed the Cloudbed by anyone who has ever laid on it. The linen is also premium quality. There is a view of the Japanese edible courtyard garden,  The container garden at the front veranda makes a cozy breakfast spot, or out the back where you can watch the chickens who laid your breakfast egg.

neighborhood_overview: Its leafy, with lovely cafes and creative shops nearby in cute Booth Street. There is even a Scientific gift shop, and the famous Sustainable Fish & Co. Sydney's "Little Italy' is down the road, in Norton St, with quirky bookshops, cinema, events and street life.
notes: I aim to make this house Five-Star value. The room is not huge, and the bathroom is shared, but its the people that you will meet and interact with that make a stay here extraordinary.  If you look at the profiles of my past guests, you will notice they are all rather wonderful. I prefer to leave rooms empty otherwise. "You are the average of the 5 people you spend the most time with".  If you are here, you are already an honoured guest.
transit: Its 4 minutes walk to the Bus stop on Parramatta road, and from there, a river of busses takes you to the city every 4 minutes or so.
access: Feel free to use the kitchen for your breakfasts, we will keep a spot for your milk etc, in the fridge.   Use of the rest of the house is by arrangement.  Check in is from 4pm.  Earlier check-ins are usually possible, just ask and we will arrange something.
interaction: I choose guests who I admire and enjoy, so our interactions are meaningful and fun.  I work from home so during the day this house becomes my home office. I also go traveling overseas regularly.  My other guests are carefully chosen by me for their lovely, creative character, and are a joy to live with, even if you hardly see each other.
house_rules: A great guest will: Keep sounds to a low-volume after 11pm Wash, dry and put away dishes immediatly after use. Wipe up all splashes in the bathroom, etc, after use. Avoid making others hear your phone conversations - pop into another room. Let us know immediatly, with a request, if you wish something was different - eg. if we are talking loudly after 11pm : ) Keep their own room generally tidy - even though we don't see it, it affects the vibe of the house. The kitchen is yours for breakfast, and by arrangement at other times. You can even bring a guest, just pre-arrange.  Use thoughtful observation, and we will all be fine. Bonus points guest: be someone with a dream you are actively persuing.   Thats usually enough to guarantee loveable excellence.
host_about:
I'm a permaculture designer and Illustrator, with a serious commitment to making my world luscious. So far, so good, thanks to the excellent people who come and stay in my house, and who let me into theirs, long before AirB&B.

I've  living and working part of each year in Australia, part in Tokyo, and little working trips all over the place.

I write a Magazine column in Japanese, 'Cecilia's Permacutlure Slow Life'. Its about creative ways to de-trap your life of wasted time, energy and affection, freeing you up to do the good work you were put on this world to do. 

For 9 years Ive run a share-house for creative people - you can read about it on my Blog Balcony Garden dreaming

My hobbies are Sado (Japanese tea eremony), balcony gardening, fancy dress parties, and drawing illustrations of the quirky world I would like to live in, and often actually do.  These are also my jobs.

Ive been a WWOOF host and traveler for many years (willing workers on organic farms). Even when my farm was just a balcony garden. 

I don't have a life motto exactly, but when thing go wrong, I ask myself 'Whiner or designer?', and that gets me positive and resourceful, finding a way to make things better.
If things go wrong for you I won't say it though. I'll just help where I can xx

name: Chez Catherine
summary: Located off the lively rue Daguerre, our clean modern flat opens on a fully equiped kitchen and a bright lounge including  daybed. Comfortable bedroom with fantastic en-suite shower room. Very parisian, off the beaten path. A great place for foodies!
space: The appartement is located 4 minutes from Denfert-Rochereau station, and  therefore is ideally connected to major places of interest served by subway lines 4 and 6, or to airports, and Eurostar, Thalys...The flat is very quiet although in the middle of a lively area of Paris.   It comprises a Kitchen with its dish-washer, fridge, freezer, cooker, oven, microwave, washing machine, a bright Lounge offering a nice view on Paris's roofs and inner gardens, a spacious Bedroom with its en-suite italian style shower-room, and plenty of cupboard space. It is a quite spacious place for 2 that can accommodate up to 4 people using the day bed.

It is a quite spacious place for 2 that can accommodate up to 4 people using the day bed. The entrance of the flat is on the 3rd floor of a newly refurbished 1920's building, in which we live. Time a
neighborhood_overview: We love Paris, every area is worth visiting. But our place is a unique village in Paris, famous for its daily fresh food market, but also its independent boutiques, great book shops, delicious bakeries, and renowned butcher Hugo Desnoyer! At your doorstep  you will enjoy typical bistros and excellent restaurants for gourmet and still affordable. It's a quick walk to Montparnasse, rue de la Gaité's Theatres, Luxembourg and l'Observatoire's Gardens,  Modern Art Cartier Foundation, Camera Obscura photo Gallery. The famous art-house cinema Denfert and Catacombs of Paris  are in close proximity!
notes: The building used to host artists' workshops (like Aki Kuroda's) and presents a very interesting architecture.
transit: With a direct acces by urban rail network RER B to Saint-Michel and Gare du Nord, Roissy Airport (50 mn), or the direct shuttle-bus to Orly airport (30 mn), this area is very easy to reach.
access: The entrance of the flat is on the 3rd floor of a newly refurbished 1920's building, in which we live. Time and weather permitting, you could enjoy a coffee or drink on our planted rooftop terrasse.
interaction: Rue Daguerre is one of the last authentic area in Paris. Very charming, full of great hidden places that you will be amazed to discover. We want you to feel at home in Paris and are just here to help! We speak French, English and Japanese.
house_rules: Non smoking guests please. The parking is in extra and needs to be discussed before booking.
host_about:
Je suis française et cosmopolite, ayant eu la chance de voyager et de vivre à l'étranger. Après Tokyo, Londres je suis désormais basée à Paris où je serais heureuse de vous accueillir et vous faire découvrir le quartier autour de la rue Daguerre, un des plus charmants villages parisiens. Je vis avec ma famille sur place et le dernier étage de l'immeuble ouvre sur une terrasse arborée où vous serez les bienvenus pour un prendre un verre ou un café si le temps le permet...A bientôt! Catherine
I am French but quite international as I have been very lucky to travel and live abroad. After  Tokyo, London, I am now based in Paris, where I would be happy welcoming people in one of the most charming village of Paris. I live on the roof top flat with my family, and weather and time permitting, we could share a coffee or a drink on our terrace. A bientôt! Catherine

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: The flat is located in Marylebone - one of London's chic and trendy areas where beautifully dressed men and women sip coffee or the latest health juice on the High Street. That said, Marylebone is certainly not snooty, in fact it has a very relaxed vibe. I love the great transport links at Baker Street and Marylebone Station which are only 5 mins away. There are also numerous buses that one can catch from Baker Street that will take you to all parts of town. Some of my favourite things to do in the area is to stroll down Marylebone High Street all the way to Bond Street. There are many lovely interior design stores and fashion stores. You can find brands such as J. Crew, Anthropologie, Whistles, Claudie Pierlot etc. on the High Street. Then there are loads of lovely cafes and restaurants scattered around the area. Here are some of the ones that I like: - Opso does small Greek tapas - Coco momo is a friendly modern pub - Trishna - 1 Michelin star Indian place focusing on seafood (yummmm
notes: My pictures are not the best so I am getting a professional photogragher but wanted to upload these pictures to make my listing live. I do not have a dishwasher I have a washing machine, but no dryer There is no cable but the TV has Netflix, Youtube, BBC iplayer and other options on the smart TV setting The flat overlooks the street so you will hear the hustle and bustle of London from time to time, especially if the windows are open If Checkin is between 9pm and 8am there is a £40 fee
transit: The closest tube station is Marylebone but you might find it easier to go to Baker Street as there is a more choice there. It is on the Hammersmith & City, Metropolitan, Circle, Bakerloo and Jubilee lines. Thats basically covers most of London for you. If you want to go to Bond Street, Buckingham Palace, Big Ben etc. jump on the Jubilee line and you will be there in 10-15 mins. Going to Oxford Circus for shopping? No problem. Hop on to the Bakerloo line. For City works wanting to go to Moorgate, Farringdon or Liverpool Street you can take the Metropolitan or Hammersmith line.

host_about:
My house, Orchard house, is a three story semi-detached Victorian style house.  With modern, traditional and stylish English feature, the House is arranged to provide four guest bedrooms, one ensuite, one family and one share bathrooms.  All bedrooms have an abundance of natural light and include heating, hot drinks station, safe box, broadband internet access, flat screen TV, hairdryer and desk. New slippers and clean towels are provided as standard as are shampoo.

The house is situated in a prestigious conservation residential area in West London.  A mere 20 minutes from central London and Heathrow airport. 

Whether you are travelling on business or leisure with your family or friends, you will find the perfect location here. The House has easy access to the excellent local shops, restaurants, pubs, cafes and boutique shops and amenities around Chiswick High Street and a great family feel to it. Within a 5 minute walking distance of Stamford Brook tube on District Line.

No smoking, no pet and no shoes in the premises.

As the independent individuality, love for travel and sports, I started my wonderful journey of transnational life from the schooldays of university at Japan.  From Tokyo, Japan to London, England, even to Los Angeles, USA, no matter study or work, easygoing me made a group of friends worldwide.

If you are first arrived at London, why not be a guest of Orchard House, to make a friend with me, and you will know London, the juiciest city in the world by my words, within the shortest time!  If you often come to London, Orchard House will also be your warmest home in this city!

house_rules: As this is a Japanese mood house, please remove your shoes when you enter, we have solid wood flooring. In the hall you will find a storage unit for footwear with complimentary slippers that you can use.   Unfortunately, we do not accept pets. No smoking is allowed inside the Studio. No loud music after 11 pm. Please remember that this is my flat, not a hotel. I live in a quiet area so I ask that you have respect for my neighbours.  Minimum 3 Nights stay is required.  Check in is between 15h and 20h, if you arrive earlier you can leave your luggage while the Studio is being prepared. Check out time is no later 11h00.  Thank you again and “Bienvenue à PARIS!” ;-) お部屋はフローリングです。靴を脱いで入室してください。 玄関にスリッパの入った靴箱があります。どうぞご利用ください。 ベット禁止 禁煙 夜11時以降は大きな音での音楽、テレビはご遠慮ください。 ここはあくまで個人のスチュディオだということを忘れないで下さい。 閑静なアパートですのでマナーはお守りください。 ご利用は3泊以上から受け付けています。 チェックインは午後3時から午後8時までですが、荷物をお預かりできます。 チェックアウトは午前11時までにしてください。 ご理解とご協力をお願いします。
host_about:
Bienvenue to Paris!  ようこそパリへ!

I am Pedro originally from a small Caribbean Island. I love to travel “backpacker style”, to meet new people, learn and share our cultures. 

I have spent some time volunteering for MSF, a Humanitarian Medical International Organisation.

I like gadgets & technology so you will notice it in my home. I am also an marathon runner so I took the opportunity during my trips to run in several cities (Hong-Kong, Dubai, Tokyo, Paris, Limerick, Rabat, NY, London and so many others..) 

As I am often away from Paris for extended periods with my job, I decided to share my modern and secure apartment in Paris. 

I hope you will enjoy the space while you stay here. I love to learn from others, so your feedback on ways to improve the living experience & comfort in my home is important to me!

Please send me any questions or queries you may have, e.g. tips on recommended local restaurants or places to visit. I will be happy to help you.

Take a breathe now, Relax…I am there to support you during your stay in Paris!

If I am around during your stay I hope we can a chance to have a drink in a French café to share your experience.

Hope to see you in my cosy home.

ようこそパリへ!

ペドロです。カリブ海にある小さな島の出身です。バックパッカースタイルで旅行して、人との出会いや知らない文化に触れたり共有するのが好きです。

ボランティア活動で国境なき医師団に参加した経験があります。

新しいテクノロジーやガジェットが大好きで、スチュディオもそんなもので溢れています。

僕は走るのも好きで旅行先では必ずと言っていいほど走ります。いままで香港、ドバイ、東京、ぱり、ラバト、ニューヨーク、ロンドンなどいろいろなところで走りました。

仕事の関係で海外への出張が多いので僕のスチュディオを貸したいと思っています。

ぜひとも楽しい時間を過ごしてください。

宿泊してくださった方はぜひフィードバックをお願いします。そこから学んでより過ごしやすい環境作りに役立てたいと思います。

何か質問がありましたら気軽に聞いてください。

もし私がパリにいたら案内もできます。

ぜひ僕のスチュディオにいらしてください。

I am originally from Brazil, I have now lived in Japan for 12 years. I have a degree in hospitality, and I have been hosting guests in Tokyo since 2011. I am very friendly and easy-going, and I am always looking for new opportunities in the hostel business. Right now I have a few great apartments in Shinjuku, Roppongi and Shibuya in Japan. which is one of the most convenient places in Tokyo for travelers. Shinjuku station is central to the expansive network of trains in the Tokyo area, making it fast, cheap, and easy to travel almost anywhere. 
I am also renting my  new penthouse in Spain and one small flat in London and in Brazil. 
In addition the apartments I have, I can also sometimes rent my friends' apartments short-term while they are traveling. With this unique situation, we can make some great deals! 
Have a wonderful stay!

host_about:
I am a free spirited artist with a strong sense of self.  I dream big and pursue without doubt.  I love to laugh and I try not to take myself or tough situations too seriously. I'm passionate about everything I do, and try to surround myself with equally passionate people. 

I'm incredibly laid back, but I'm also very outgoing and social. I love being around people. I have traveled to most major cities in the US, and very few out of the country. However, I am ready to see the world! My dream destination is Tokyo, Japan, amongst many others. 

I love hosting and meeting new people while sharing and learning about their experiences and lives. As a host, I share my space openly and create a fun and positive environment for my guests. Everyone feels at home, and most feel as if we've known each other for a lifetime. As a guest, I am respectful, clean, interactive, cheerful and always grateful!

My motto in life is, "She who dares, wins!"

house_rules: This 2-story "Grand Old Lady" build in 1903 likes its quiet & peaceful use. There is a dog & cat at the house so please no pets. When you park on the driveway the neighbors can't get to work and will call a tow-truck at your expense. Outside smoking only. Please respect other guests sensitivity to cigarette smell. This is a home where travelers from all over the world cross paths, respect each others privacy and once in awhile watch a sunset from the deck in good company. Enjoy an Airbnb host-guest experience in a safe, residential setting without the burden of responsibilities that come with being a roommate or tenant.  There is a lock on your door but I hope you don't feel the need to use it.

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

neighborhood_overview: We are located in Downtown Los Angeles which is made up of around 15 different neighborhoods or districts, each with their own subtle character and personalities. We are in The Old Bank District which is a sub-district of sorts of The Historic Core, which contains some of the oldest buildings and architecture in the city. The neighborhood is a lively and fascinating place!  Downtown LA is very urban, and with that comes many wonderful and not so wonderful things. Some of the wonderful things are the museums–like MOCA, The Broad, The Geffen Contemporary, and The Japanese American National Museum that are all within walking distance. There are numerous world class art galleries, restaurants, and coffee bars nearby. Downtown is really the only place in LA where you feel like you are in a city. Our neighborhood is incredibly diverse and colorful. It contains populations from just about every ethnic background, age range and economic strata. In recent years we’ve had an abundance of amazing
notes: This is a REAL loft, not a shiny new apartment masquerading as a loft. While we have done a tremendous job making it somewhat luxurious and comfortable, there are some funky things to note.  This is a brick building with no insulation. The windows have thin glass and no screens. We find it lovely for fresh air and a nice breeze, but this means we get an occasional fly or mosquito buzzing about. It also gets city dusty real fast and as much as we try, its hard to keep up. The loft is warm in the summer and cool in the winter. The floors are gorgeous old barn wood that we installed ourselves and sometimes a board becomes loose or uneven, so be careful walking around with bare feet. The shower is a comedy of old tiles. We keep it very clean but its not the most glamorous shower in LA. The shower is located behind a folding partition, adjacent to the kitchen and living room–mostly private, but not in an enclosed room with a lockable door way. Walking distance to METRO subway trains and our new METRO Bike Share, where you can conveniently rent European style city bikes and bounce around the downtown districts–a great way to see the sights and enjoy our beautiful weather! There are trains and buses all around to take you to Hollywood or the west side. We are also a short ride from Union Station where trains can be caught to San Francisco, San Diego or anywhere else in the States. access: Our home is in a unique 3-story building with no call box or automated entry system and locked up like a fortress. Guests are required to schedule their arrival so we may greet you and give you access to the building.  Once inside, there are 3 flights of stairs to reach the loft on the top floor. There, we will give you a quick tour of the space and your lovely room.   The guest bedroom is a part of a large loft that has one other private bedroom where we stay. The room has shutter style doors with a simple latch lock on the inside. We have these doors so that in case of an emergency, anyone who is in the loft will have access to the fire escape which is located off the guest room. Just outside of the two bedrooms is our office area, where we work when we are not in the gallery. Our office area and bedroom are off limits to our guests.   We provide coffee or tea and some easy going breakfast food so you have nice start to your day. Use of the kitchen is limited to light meals and guest
interaction: Los Angeles is a big city with much to see and do–we will be happy to make recommendations and explain directions. Our art gallery and store are located on the second floor of the building, so we are usually around to answer any questions or help when needed. We enjoy cooking and the occasional glass of wine or cocktail, and are usually home in the evenings.
house_rules: - Please respect our space as if it were your own home.  - No additional guests day or night without advance permission of host. - This is a drug free environment. Absolutely no drugs permitted. - No filming or photography permitted without consent of host. - Please keep your personal belongings in the guest room.  - Use of the kitchen is limited to light meals and you must provide your own provisions. Anything more must be agreed to with host. - When using the kitchen please clean up straight away. - A small, friendly Yorkshire Terrier lives here too. Although this breed is said to be hypoallergenic, if you are highly allergic or don't care for pets we recommend booking elsewhere. - We welcome any feedback that could help us improve the experience for you and others.
host_about: My husband and I are both fourth generation Angelenos who grew up in the surf and sand of nearby Southern California beach towns. While working in the photography business, we became friends on a job in 2003 and married 4 years later in a remote temple outside of Chiang Mai, Thailand. We live in an amazing 129 year old brick building in the heart of Downtown Los Angeles where we own and operate an art gallery and store with a tiny dog named Mac. We love to travel, meet people and experience new places.

host_about:
Hi! 

I’ve lived in San Francisco for 21 years now, prior to which I lived in Asia (Tokyo, Japan to be specific). I also consider myself a citizen of the world, as I have traveled to 49 countries so far and in addition to English, speak some Japanese and French. 

In my travels, I have stayed at some amazing places and know what a difference great hospitality can make to a trip. I therefore strive to create an experience at Bali Hai Castro that will be memorable and unique. My aim is that you will come back each time you return to San Francisco to stay here agin. 

I know the city and surrounding area very well and am always happy to give suggestions to make your stay exceptional. I am also a foodie and am working on a type of food blog — so if you are looking for great restaurants, I can share with you my favorites.

As a guest, I am responsible, trustworthy, and neat. Being a host myself, I can completely put myself in your shoes and am very respectful of your space. I love AirBNB because it really affords one the opportunity to live like a local when you travel to a new area.

In my free time, I enjoy spending time with my puppy (Dexter), working out, hiking, traveling, skiing, and generally making the most of life. 

If you are considering booking my home, I know you will love your stay here!

If I have made a reservation request with you, I can promise that you will be delighted to have me as a guest.

Hope to meet you soon,

Laurence

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

host_about:
My name is Fabio and I along with my friend and colleague Willian will ensure to provide you a wonderful stay in our apartments across London.

Willian, Throughout his extensive travels, his unusual name – a derivative of William – has led to much curiosity. An Ecuadorian by birth, He has added to my higher education internationally, with economic studies in the USA, language training in Japan, and a BA and MBA in the United Kingdom.

I am a 37 year old professional, currently working and living in London, Willian is 30 year old professional, currently working and living in lively London. the most exciting and bigger property market in the world. During all this description of myself well mostly Willian, you will find out how travelling could probably be Willian's and I number 1 hobbie. Although, We do not see it as a hobby but a luxury :). We do also enjoy playing sports, attending concerts, going to the movies, clubbing, hanging out, cooking and much more! 

Airbnb is awesome. Willian remembers his first time using the portal was back in 2010, when he travelled to Tokyo to attend an university interview over there. He had booked an comfortable duplex apartment in Shinjuku from this lovely Japanese guy, Junichi. He was amazed to see the true meaning of hospitality, being a host is more than just being the doorman or the typical receptionist at concierge, it is being someone who receives, treat and entertains other people as guests. 

All my life Willian and I have dedicated quite a lot of time to travel around the globe where We have had the opportunity to meet amazing people and experienced other cultures, costumes, and more. That is exactly why I am currently working in the hospitality industry with my colleague and friend Fabio because what I have learned all these years travelling around is that hospitality is the friendly and generous reception and entertainment of guests, visitors, or strangers not matter where people come from.

Fabio and I look forward welcoming and hosting some many guest in the upcoming years. I will truly give you my 100% to ensure your stay goes very well why you are staying at my apartments. I hope you enjoy the experience and adventure and thank you in advance :).

Your hosts,
Willian - Fabio

house_rules: 1.  The apartment will be all yours so please take good care of it. 2.  Please be quiet and discreet.  Very important to respect your neighbors in Japan as everyone lives close together!  Absolutely no partying in the unit.  Please enjoy yourself outside and make new friends.   3.  You must turn off the air conditioner/heater when not there. 4.  Please take off your shoes when you enter. 5.  NO SMOKING inside the apartment.  Outside on the balcony is fine.  Standing and smoking in front of the building entrance is not allowed.  Please dispose of your buds properly.  Do not put in recyclable cans or bottles. 6.  SELF CHECK-IN:  For your convenience and privacy this is a self-catering unit. It is your responsibility to find the place.  Don't worry because I give very detailed and accurate directions in the confirmation. 7.  This is NOT a HOTEL:   As such, you cannot ask anyone in the building for assistance. My team and I are always available between the hours of 7 AM and 1 AM  via Airbn
host_about:
Nice to meet you.  My name is Will.  I love hosting on airbnb and it is my life.  It is tons of fun and there are new surprises every day!  I have met so many interesting people as a host and I look forward to those I will meet in the future.  

I am a sports fan, reader, movie goer, and I like to try new things.  I play golf, basketball, and just about any sport you can think of.  I love ramen, yakiniku, yakitori, and shabu shabu here in Japan.   I love to try pizza all over the world when I travel.   

Relationships are the most important thing for me in my personal life as well as business.  I like to go out and have a good time with my friends and meet new people.  

I have learned so much from my over three years as an airbnb host and I am pleased to say I have most questions answered for you before you ask them, whether it be in the description of the listing or in the detail I supply you with at confirmation.  Still, I am always thinking of ways to make the guest experience more comfortable, efficient, and hassle free.   This is my goal as a host.  I will continue to get more places every month so I can host more travelers.  I want everyone to see Tokyo at least once!   

Tokyo is a great place to come and people from all over the world visit here making it a truly international city.  I love Tokyo and seeing the amazing sights and people.  It is a great place to explore and every day can be different.  This is an awesome destination for walkers and wanders filled with friendly people, tasty restaurants, and plenty of lights.   My tip is to make the initial contact with Japanese people because they are typically shy at first.   They will be happy to try to practice their English with you.

Hope I can host you soon!  May your trip to Tokyo be as amazing as my 7 years here has been!
street: Peel Street, Hong Kong, Hong Kong Island, Hong Kong
